</table>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://mathdl.maa.org/convergence/1/?pa=content&amp;sa=viewDocument&amp;nodeId=196&amp;bodyId=60" class="external text" title="http://mathdl.maa.org/convergence/1/?pa=content&amp;sa=viewDocument&amp;nodeId=196&amp;bodyId=60" rel="nofollow">Derivations of Conic Sections</a> at <a href="http://mathdl.maa.org/convergence/1/" class="external text" title="http://mathdl.maa.org/convergence/1/" rel="nofollow">Convergence</a></li>
<li><a href="http://xahlee.org/SpecialPlaneCurves_dir/ConicSections_dir/conicSections.html" class="external text" title="http://xahlee.org/SpecialPlaneCurves_dir/ConicSections_dir/conicSections.html" rel="nofollow">Conic sections</a> at <a href="http://xahlee.org/SpecialPlaneCurves_dir/specialPlaneCurves.html" class="external text" title="http://xahlee.org/SpecialPlaneCurves_dir/specialPlaneCurves.html" rel="nofollow">Special plane curves</a>.</li>
<li><cite id="Reference-Mathworld-Conic_Section"><a href="/wiki/Eric_W._Weisstein" title="Eric W. Weisstein">Eric W. Weisstein</a>, <i><a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/ConicSection.html" class="external text" title="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/ConicSection.html" rel="nofollow">Conic Section</a></i> at <a href="/wiki/MathWorld" title="MathWorld">MathWorld</a>.</cite></li>
<li><a href="http://math.fullerton.edu/mathews/n2003/ConicFitMod.html" class="external text" title="http://math.fullerton.edu/mathews/n2003/ConicFitMod.html" rel="nofollow">Determinants and Conic Section Curves</a></li>
<li><a href="http://britton.disted.camosun.bc.ca/jbconics.htm" class="external text" title="http://britton.disted.camosun.bc.ca/jbconics.htm" rel="nofollow">Occurrence of the conics. Conics in nature and elsewhere</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mathacademy.com/pr/prime/articles/conics/index.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.mathacademy.com/pr/prime/articles/conics/index.asp" rel="nofollow">Conics</a>. An essay on conics and how they are generated.</li>
<li>See <a href="http://www.cut-the-knot.org/proofs/conics.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.cut-the-knot.org/proofs/conics.shtml" rel="nofollow">Conic Sections</a> at <a href="http://www.cut-the-knot.org" class="external text" title="http://www.cut-the-knot.org" rel="nofollow">cut-the-knot</a> for a sharp proof that any finite conic section is an ellipse and <a href="http://xahlee.org/PageTwo_dir/more.html" class="external text" title="http://xahlee.org/PageTwo_dir/more.html" rel="nofollow">Xah Lee</a> for a similar treatment of other conics.</li>
</ul>


